---
import StatusBadge from "../components/StatusBadge.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About the Enterprise Reality Programme, its research-first development approach and current public status."
  canonicalPath="/about/"
>
  <section class="page-hero section">
    <div class="container page-hero__inner">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1>The Enterprise Reality Programme</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Enterprise Reality was created to address the architectural gap
          between operational enterprise systems and the governed understanding
          needed for explainable decisions and authorised action.
        </p>
      </div>
      <aside class="panel">
        <h2>Programme status</h2>
        <StatusBadge status="In Development" />
        <p>
          The public website and platform programme are under active
          development. Live operating status and commercial availability are
          outside WEB-1.1.
        </p>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--muted" aria-labelledby="story-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <p class="eyebrow">Programme Story</p>
        <h2 id="story-heading">Research-first architecture, then software</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid--2">
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Why it was created</h3>
          <p>
            Enterprise Reality began from the observation that enterprise change
            often proceeds before organisations have a shared, governed account
            of what is true, what is evidenced and what is authorised.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>The architectural problem</h3>
          <p>
            Operational systems are necessary, but they usually encode partial
            views of identity, evidence, policy and decision authority. The
            programme addresses the need for a constitutional layer across those
            views.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Research-first development</h3>
          <p>
            The programme develops through publications, architecture decisions,
            platform layers, implementation stories, tests and review evidence.
            Software follows governed meaning.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Architecture and software</h3>
          <p>
            Architecture defines responsibilities and boundaries. Software
            implements those boundaries through small, testable capabilities
            without redefining the constitutional model.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="founder-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <p class="eyebrow">Founder</p>
        <h2 id="founder-heading">Sheriff Oyekanmi</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="lead">
        Enterprise Reality is founded by Sheriff Oyekanmi. This public website
        uses approved programme information only and does not publish personal
        contact details.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
